{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "10", "m": "05", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "22", "M": "34", "S": "40"}}, "news": [{"title": "Goa's town planning department to lock 82 lakh sq meters under no-development zones", "para": "Goa's TCP department is designating over 82.8 lakh sqm of land as non-developable, marking a significant move to protect ecologically sensitive areas. This initiative, driven by forest department recommendations, aims to preserve natural cover, sand dunes, orchards, and water bodies across Salcete, Mormugao, Sattari, and Pernem for future generations.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/goa-designates-82-lakh-sqm-as-no-development-zones-to-protect-ecological-areas/130993527?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-126296/130993527.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "PMRDA likely to hand over Mahalunge-Maan town planning scheme to PMC for implementation", "para": "The stalled Mahalunge-Maan Town Planning scheme is finally progressing. The Pune Metropolitan Region Development Authority will transfer the project's execution to the Pune Municipal Corporation. This move follows the merger of villages into PMC limits. The scheme aims to develop a 250-hectare area near Hinjewadi IT park. It promises improved infrastructure and planned urban growth for the region.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/mahalunge-maan-town-planning-scheme-to-be-handed-over-to-pmc-after-8-year-delay/130993497?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-235210/130993497.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Hubballi-Dharwad civic body extends 5% property tax rebate till May-end", "para": "The Hubballi-Dharwad Municipal Corporation has extended its 5% property tax rebate until the end of May due to lower-than-expected collections. The drive began late, prompting the extension to boost the Rs 235 crore target for 2026-27, with Rs 90 crore collected so far. GIS work will also be offered free in July and August.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/hubballi-dharwad-municipal-corporation-extends-5-property-tax-rebate-until-may-31/130991917?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-65756/130991917.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}